notes: the Pt coil at the bottom of the CE bong block it off. 01... whoa! sample seems way to active, or the RE_vs_RHE has shifted. But how??? Maybe I needed the 10 Ohm. Really ugly O2 peak shapes, unusable data. I'm quite confident that M/Z=32 was air, since it has the exact same shape and height as a later m/z=32 spike at 4770 sm The m/z=34 signal perfectly follows the m/z=36 except for during the air spike, where it overshoots an amount that I'm sure corresponds to the air signal. So despite small flaws in the data, I'm confident this supports our consistent observation of no lattice exchange on this material. 02...
